<item>
            <title>[HBASE-5534] HBase shell&apos;s return value is almost always 0</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-5534</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;So I was trying to write some simple scripts to verify client connections to HBase using the shell and I noticed that the HBase shell always returns 0 even when it can&apos;t connect to an HBase server. I&apos;m not sure if this is the best option. What would be neat is if you had some capability to run commands like&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;hbase shell --command=&apos;disable table;\ndrop table;&apos; and it would error out if any of the commands fail to succeed. echo &quot;disable table&quot; | hbase shell could continue to work as it does now.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
